  "text": "Reception is the realm where ideologies are reproduced and potentially challenged. In some types and parts of media content, capital is accumulated by selling the audience as commodity to advertising clients. Dallas Smythe (1981 Smythe ( /2006 spoke in this context of the audience commodity. As advertising profits are not a general feature of all media capital, there is a dotted line in figure 2 that signifies the audience commodity. In recent times, recipients have increasingly become an active audience that produces content and technologies. In this context, the notion of produsers (producer + user) and prosumers (producer + consumer) can be employed. Produsage and prosumage can both advance media capital accumulation [CITATION_1] and alternative media production.",
